<marquee class="dckimPixelMono" style="position: fixed; z-index: 9999999999; bottom: 0px; left: 0px; width: 100%; height: 6px; background-color: white; color: black; font-size: 6px; display: none; padding-top: 1px;" title="i wonder if anyone notices this now that it is only small..." onclick="this.style.display='none';">
Certainly, such a small marquee will be allowed to exist, and not be subject to the wanton eradication that has befalled so many a marquee before it...
Maybe this tiniest little marquee can be used to preserve the proud history of the scrolling HTML marquee element...
The history of the scrolling marquee is a very long story which is far too long to be contained within a scrolling marquee.
It would actually be a disservice to the scrolling marquee itself and the lengthy tale of it's interesting history to attempt to tell the entire story of it's history inside of a simple scrolling marquee...
And even so as the length of the text that is placed within the confines of the scrolling marquee is not technically limited in quantity, and neither is the breadth or height limiting the contents,
it still does not seem to be up to the task of presenting a complete documentary history of scrolling marquee. Maybe one day someone will write such a history and publish it but, most likely it's format will not itself be a scrolling marquee...
</marquee>


